docs.lead_paragraph: The halt of an official investigation has not quieted questions over how hundreds of millions of dollars ended up in the accounts of Prime Minister Najib Razak.
docs.abstract: Malaysian Atty Gen Mohamed Apandi Ali's statement clearing Prime Min Najib Razak of corruption charges involving transfer of hundreds of millions of dollars to his bank account has provided more questions than answers; Ali says largest sum in question, $681 million, was donation from Saudi royal family that was later returned, claim that some doubt.

headline.main: No End to Scrutiny Over Millions Sent to Malaysian Leader’s Accounts
headline.print_headline: Another Inquiry Ends, but Scrutiny of Malaysian Leader’s Finances Persists

byline.contributor: Ben Hubbard contributed reporting from Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, and Nick Cumming-Bruce from Geneva.

docs.lead_paragraph: Bernard Aronson, who played a role in American policy in Nicaragua and El Salvador, is back in the diplomatic field, trying to end the guerrilla conflict in Colombia.
docs.abstract: Saturday Profile of Bernard Aronson, diplomat serving as Pres Obama's special envoy to peace talks between Colombian government and Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia, or FARC; Aronson has extensive experience as negotiator in Latin America and seeks to end 50-year conflict.

headline.main: A Democratic Diplomat, at Ease With Both Guerrillas and the G.O.P.
headline.print_headline: Veteran Diplomat Takes a Quiet but Crucial Role in Colombia

docs.snippet: In a 2014 race, Scott Brown struck a chord with New Hampshire voters uneasy with border issues. Mr. Brown lost, but he may have set the tone for Mr. Trump....
docs.lead_paragraph: In a 2014 race, Scott Brown struck a chord with New Hampshire voters uneasy with border issues. Mr. Brown lost, but he may have set the tone for Mr. Trump.
docs.abstract: Donald Trump's surprising showing in race for Republican presidential nomination, which has leveraged strong stance on illegal immigration, was in many ways presaged by Scott Brown's success in 2014 race for New Hampshire Senate seat; Brown, who has endorsed Trump, survived much of crowded primary by appealing to concerns of working-class voters who held strong views on immigration.

headline.main: Donald Trump’s Immigration Message May Resound in New Hampshire
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Stance on Borders Might Stir New Hampshire
